history.content: Yes, Campus Solutions (sic) will force you to drop off the waitlist and re-add yourself to the end of the waitlist to be able to switch non-enrollment sections like labs or discussions.  It may still work out for the best but that is what will happen.

I am currently on the waitlist for 61C despite having originally enrolled in open sections (I'm guessing that the number of open seats for L&S undeclared students filled up). So I was wondering if there's any way that I can switch my lab time to an open one instead (and maybe get off the waitlist in the process) since my original sections are now full. I'm just worried that if I drop 61C and re-enroll, I'll lost my position on the waitlist. Thank you!
history.subject: CS 61C Switching Lab Times
